note._content: "RIVER OF DOUBT" -- Former U. S. President Theodore Roosevelt had recently returned from a harrowing trip to South America, where, in a dugout canoe, he had traversed the hitherto-unexplored "River of Doubt," (part of the Amazon network) which was renamed "Rio Roosevelt" in his honor. TR was then lecturing about his ordeal, and would write a book about it.
note.author: 70251312@N00

note._content: Presumably a 1914 Princeton University publication will tell us what this grisly tableau represents?
